					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd say make it mapper #7, submapper #1, so every emulator that currently exists will be able run the rom without the user manually needing to change the mapper number to 7.  There are a LOT of NES emulators out there.  Emulators may appear on unexpected platforms, like the TI Nspire, Playstation 1, Dreamcast, in-car DVD player, and the list goes on.  Emulators are often abandoned, and modifying emulators to support a new mapper is not always a possibility.</div>

					
